radiographic_examinations.findings: The appendix is mildly dilated measuring up to 8 mm with a mildly thick and enhancing wall. There is mild periappendiceal fat stranding. Imaged lung bases are clear. No pleural or pericardial effusion. The liver enhances homogeneously without focal lesion. No intra- or extra-hepatic biliary dilatation. Gallbladder, spleen, pancreas, and adrenal glands are normal. Loops of small bowel are normal in caliber. The kidneys enhance and excrete contrast symmetrically, without hydronephrosis. No free air or free fluid. Few subcentimeter mesenteric lymph nodes without CT criteria for pathologic enlargement.
